# Normalize line endings across platforms.
#
# Without this, contributors on Windows with `git config --global core.autocrlf true`
# end up with CRLF in their working tree, which conflicts with .prettierrc's
# `endOfLine: "lf"` — prettier --check fails and prettier --write produces
# diffs that flip every line back to LF.
#
# `* text=auto eol=lf` tells git to:
#   - detect text files automatically (text=auto)
#   - store them as LF in the repo (always)
#   - check them out as LF in the working tree regardless of core.autocrlf (eol=lf)
#
# Binary files are still detected and left alone via text=auto.

* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicit binary patterns — belt and suspenders so these are never
# accidentally line-ending-normalized even if git's heuristic misfires.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.svg binary
*.pdf binary
*.zip binary
*.gz binary
*.tar binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
*.eot binary
*.mp3 binary
*.mp4 binary
*.webm binary
*.wav binary
*.avif binary
